"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983246","Home Office","false","2018-10-16","<p>In this Parliament, the Inter-Ministerial Group (IMG) on Anti-Corruption met on 2 July 2018 and is next scheduled to meet on 14 November 2018. The IMG guides the UK’s overall efforts to combat corruption and its corrosive effects, primarily by scrutinising implementation of the December 2017 cross-government UK Anti-Corruption Strategy and driving specific cross-Whitehall policy initiatives<em>.</em></p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2018-10-16T12:40:16.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983246/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983246/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-08","Anti-corruption Ministerial Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, on what dates the anti-corruption inter-ministerial group has held meetings.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","176552"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983247","Treasury","false","2018-10-12","<p>Treasury ministers and officials have regular discussions with our counterparts in the Scottish Government on matters of importance to Scotland’s economy and the wider UK.</p><p> </p><p>Derek Mackay, Cabinet Secretary for Finance, Economy and Fair Work in the Scottish Government, wrote to the Chancellor of the Exchequer on 1 May setting out plans for the Scottish National Investment Bank. Officials subsequently met to discuss the Scottish Government’s proposals.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","176328","2018-10-12T10:28:04.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983247/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/983247/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-10-08","Banks: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions his Department has held with the Scottish Government on the establishment of the Scottish National Investment Bank.","false","Biography information for Kirsty Blackman","Aberdeen North","Kirsty Blackman","176327"
