"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980145","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-10-15","<p>The Foreign Secretary visited Burma in September and saw for himself the destruction caused by the Burmese Army brutal clearance operations in Rakhine. We want justice to be done for crimes under international law committed in Burma. We will continue to work with our international partners to ensure this, exploring all options. We are working in the UN Security Council to ensure accountability, including by looking at the option of an ad hoc tribunal, while also pushing for accelerated progress on refugee returns. We assess that there is not currently sufficient support within the Security Council for the creation of an ad hoc tribunal.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-10-15T14:53:53.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980145/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980145/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980145/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-01","Burma: Crimes against Humanity","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they support the creation of an ad hoc international criminal tribunal for crimes under international law committed in Myanmar, including alleged genocide, crimes against humanity and war crimes.","false","Biography information for Baroness Helic",,"Baroness Helic","HL10414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980146","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p>The Department has made no such estimate.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-10-15T13:57:03.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980146/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980146/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980146/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust: DeepMind","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what estimate they have made of the cost to the public of inquiries by the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO), National Data Guardian, Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency, and NHS Digital, resulting from the agreement for the Royal Free Hospital to provide data to DeepMind which the ICO found to be unlawful.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL10415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980147","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p>The proposals outlined in the recent consultation, <em>Proposed changes to the statutory scheme to control the costs of branded health service medicines</em>, ensure that the scheme can continue to fulfil its purpose of safeguarding the financial position of the National Health Service, alongside the voluntary Pharmaceutical Price Regulation Scheme. A copy of the consultation document is attached. The proposals set out in the recent consultation are aimed at constraining the cost of branded health service medicines to a level that balances the interests of patients, the NHS, industry and the taxpayer. The consultation’s impact assessment demonstrates significant overall benefits to patient health, driven by the reinvestment of any savings generated from the statutory scheme in NHS budgets. A copy of the impact assessment, <em>2018 Statutory Scheme for Branded Medicines Pricing</em>, is attached.</p><p>There is a wider framework in place to ensure the cost-effectiveness of medicines used in the NHS, most importantly, through National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) appraisals. This existing framework remains unchanged by the proposals set out in the consultation, with the NHS still required to fund all medicines approved through a NICE technology appraisal. The Department is committed to ensuring access to clinically and cost-effective medicines, and is working with NHS England and the pharmaceutical industry to support improvements in the speed and rate of access to new medicines for NHS patients.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","HL10417","2018-10-15T10:59:00.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980147/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980147/answer","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.pdf ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.pdf ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Proposed changes to the statutory scheme ; Statutory Scheme Impact Assessment","Proposed changes to the statutory scheme ; Statutory Scheme Impact Assessment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980147/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","NHS: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how the proposed statutory scheme for branded drugs will improve access to cost-effective medicines for patients in the UK.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL10416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980148","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p>The proposals outlined in the recent consultation, <em>Proposed changes to the statutory scheme to control the costs of branded health service medicines</em>, ensure that the scheme can continue to fulfil its purpose of safeguarding the financial position of the National Health Service, alongside the voluntary Pharmaceutical Price Regulation Scheme. A copy of the consultation document is attached. The proposals set out in the recent consultation are aimed at constraining the cost of branded health service medicines to a level that balances the interests of patients, the NHS, industry and the taxpayer. The consultation’s impact assessment demonstrates significant overall benefits to patient health, driven by the reinvestment of any savings generated from the statutory scheme in NHS budgets. A copy of the impact assessment, <em>2018 Statutory Scheme for Branded Medicines Pricing</em>, is attached.</p><p>There is a wider framework in place to ensure the cost-effectiveness of medicines used in the NHS, most importantly, through National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) appraisals. This existing framework remains unchanged by the proposals set out in the consultation, with the NHS still required to fund all medicines approved through a NICE technology appraisal. The Department is committed to ensuring access to clinically and cost-effective medicines, and is working with NHS England and the pharmaceutical industry to support improvements in the speed and rate of access to new medicines for NHS patients.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","HL10416","2018-10-15T10:59:00.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980148/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980148/answer","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.pdf ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.pdf ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Proposed changes to the statutory scheme ; Statutory Scheme Impact Assessment","Proposed changes to the statutory scheme ; Statutory Scheme Impact Assessment","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980148/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","NHS: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the proposals outlined in the draft branded drugs statutory scheme will improve access to innovative medicines in the UK.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL10417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980149","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p>The Government is committed to supporting the United Kingdom life sciences industry as one of the most innovative and internationally competitive sectors of our economy. The statutory scheme is one component in the wider UK medicines landscape, and covers companies who do not sign up to the voluntary scheme (currently the 2014 Pharmaceutical Price Regulation Scheme).</p><p>The impact assessment accompanying the recent <em>Proposed changes to the statutory scheme to control the costs of branded health medicines </em>consultation, concluded that the impact on the UK economy of any foregone research and development investment in response to lower pharmaceutical revenues would be limited, with a net present value impact of -£2.4 million over 2019 to 2021. This is outweighed by positive impacts from reinvesting any savings in the National Health Service leading to net monetised benefits of £1,167 million over the same period. Copies of the consultation document and the impact assessment, <em>2018 Statutory Scheme – Branded Medicines Pricing</em>, are attached.</p><p>The Department has received a number of responses to its recent consultation by members of the public, NHS bodies, industry organisations, as well as individual companies. In considering the responses, the Department will carefully take into account any evidence submitted on the potential impact on the UK life science sector.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-10-15T13:58:07.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980149/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980149/answer","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.pdf ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.pdf ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.p ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","Statutory_Scheme_Consultation_Document_corrected.p ; 2018_Statutory_Scheme_Impact_Assessment_1.pdf","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980149/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","NHS: Drugs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how the proposed statutory scheme for branded drugs will enhance the position of the UK as a key centre for the life sciences industry.","false","Biography information for Lord Hunt of Kings Heath",,"Lord Hunt of Kings Heath","HL10418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980150","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-10-15","<p>​The UK supports freedom of religious belief for all Yemenis. On 28 September the UK voted for a resolution at the UN Human Rights Council that emphasised the international community’s concern at the plight of the Baha’i and called for the immediate release of all Baha’i detained due to their religious belief. The persecution of members of the Baha’i community in areas of Yemen under Houthi control due to their religious beliefs is a serious violation of international human rights law. New cases of arbitrary detention and continuing reports of the abuse of detainees by the Houthis are deeply concerning, and we wholly condemn this mistreatment. We have raised our concerns with the Houthi authorities.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-10-15T14:32:42.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980150/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980150/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980150/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-01","Yemen: Baha'i Faith","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what steps they are taking to ensure that members of the Baha’i faith in prison or facing death sentences by Houthi courts in Yemen are protected.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL10419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980151","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>There are no active vaccination programmes against smallpox or anthrax for any of the emergency services.</p><p>Vaccines can be made available to first responders responding to a confirmed anthrax incident if required. The Government still holds the smallpox vaccine for use against certain strains of orthopox viruses if required.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-10-15T10:54:32.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980151/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980151/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980151/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","Vaccination: Emergency Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many members of each of the emergency services have been vaccinated against (1) smallpox, and (2) anthrax; what percentage of the total staff of each service this represents; and of those vaccinated, how many will need to be vaccinated again in the next year.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL10420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980152","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p>The Government has not undertaken or commissioned research in this area. However, the National Institute for Health Research and the Medical Research Council both have a wide portfolio of research activity in vaccines which support underpinning vaccine research and new vaccine technologies, through to clinical trials.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-10-15T10:56:26.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980152/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980152/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980152/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","Horsepox: Vaccination","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what research they have undertaken or commissioned into the creation of an effective vaccine against the synthetic horsepox virus.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL10421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980153","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-15","<p>Clostridium botulinum toxin is the active substance used as a starting material for the manufacture of Botox, a licensed human medicine. Active substances are those substances which give a medicinal product its therapeutic effect and must be manufactured to Good Manufacturing Practice standards for active substances used as a starting material.</p><p>From 20 August 2013, manufacturers, importers and distributors of active substances who are established in the United Kingdom had to register their activity with the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency.</p><p>The UK has no registered importers of the active substance Clostridium botulinum toxin, but has one registered manufacturer of the toxin that is Good Manufacturing Practice compliant, and was last inspected in May 2016.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2018-10-15T10:57:06.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980153/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980153/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980153/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-01","Botulinum Toxin: Imports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many import licences or permissions were granted in each of the last five years for live botulin toxins for the manufacture of Botox.","false","Biography information for Lord Jopling",,"Lord Jopling","HL10422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980154","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>We base our assessments on official inflation rates that are published by the Office for National Statistics (ONS) for a wide range of UK industries, as well as the Department's own contract and personnel data. Typically, we use around 80 different ONS price indices.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-10-15T15:07:58.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980154/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980154/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980154/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-01","Defence: Inflation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what indices Government departments use when calculating defence inflation.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL10423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980155","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>At 1 April 2018 the Department expected to use 11.5 billion Euros in the 10 years from 2018-19 and had placed forward contracts for the value of 2.1 billion Euros in the three years from 2018-19 using services provided by the Bank of England.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-10-15T15:08:17.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980155/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980155/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-01","Defence: Procurement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is the value of the exposure of the Ministry of Defence to fluctuations in the value of the euro against the sterling; and how much of that exposure is hedged externally.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL10424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980156","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) undertakes substantial purchases of fuel commodities, the price of which will be influenced by oil prices. The Department secures a degree of protection against changes in price by purchasing hedging contracts that are equivalent to buying a proportion of forecast demand at agreed prices in advance.</p><p>The MOD hedges up to three years in advance and usually trades quarterly to further spread price risk. This approach has been used for fuel hedging since 2010.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-10-15T15:08:31.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980156/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980156/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980156/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-01","Defence: Procurement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what are the implications for the defence budget of rising oil prices.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL10425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980157","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>At 1 April 2018 the Department expected to use 34 billion US Dollars in the 10 years from 2018-19 and had placed forward contracts for the value of 5.6 billion US Dollars in the three years from 2018-19 using services provided by the Bank of England.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-10-15T15:09:14.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980157/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980157/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980157/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-01","Defence: Procurement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is the value of the exposure of the Ministry of Defence to fluctuations in the value of the US dollar against sterling: and how much of that exposure is hedged externally.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL10426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980158","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>A decision on whether to refuel HMS Victorious will be announced in due course. There are no plans to refuel HMS Vigilant or HMS Vengeance.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-10-15T15:09:33.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980158/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980158/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-01","Trident Submarines","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what plans they have for refuelling its SSBN fleet beyond contracts already placed.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL10427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980159","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-15","<p>The UK has taken delivery of 16 F-35B Lightning aircraft from the manufacturer of which nine are currently based in the UK with 617 Squadron and seven are in the US.</p><p>617 Squadron is on track for Initial Operating Capability from land by the end of 2018, at which time it will have a preliminary complement of nine aircraft fully capable of undertaking operations from the land.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2018-10-15T14:54:23.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980159/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980159/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-01","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many F-35 Lightning aircraft have been handed over by the manufacturer; how many are in the UK and how many are still in the USA; when Initial Operating Capability of the aircraft when land based is expected; and how many aircraft will be available for operations when Initial Operating Capability is achieved.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL10428"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980160","Home Office","false","2018-10-10","<p>We have confidence in UNHCR’s systems and the agreed submission categories upon which they refers cases to the UK government to be considered for resettlement. UNHCR is the internationally recognised and mandated agency for dealing with refugees: it has a global presence and 65 years’ experience in handling refugee crises, and is best placed to identify and refer the most vulnerable refugees for resettlement.</p><p>Looking to the future, we have begun work with key stakeholders and international organisations on our future Asylum and Resettlement Strategy, which includes consideration of a future resettlement offer, post-2020.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2018-10-10T13:45:52.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980160/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980160/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-01","Refugees: LGBT People","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what consideration they have given to including sexual orientation and gender identity as additional vulnerability criteria alongside UNHCR's criteria for future resettlement programmes.","false","Biography information for Lord Scriven",,"Lord Scriven","HL10429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980161","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-10-15","<p>​The Intergrated Activity Fund is not an investment fund. The technical assistance that we provide to Bahrain supports the building of effective and accountable institutions, including strengthening the rule of law and police and judicial reform. Government programmes are regularly reviewed to ensure that they continue to offer value for money and are delivering UK objectives.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-10-15T14:59:57.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980161/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980161/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-01","Bahrain: Technical Assistance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they will review suspending investment in Bahrain through the Integrated Activity Fund.","false","Biography information for Lord Scriven",,"Lord Scriven","HL10430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980162","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-10-15","<p>​The UK has been providing a range of technical and practical assistance to the Government of Bahrain since 2012 in support of its reform programme. Each programme and project funded by the British Government goes through a rigorous compliance process before commencement. The content of this process is not disclosed, as we have stated in previous replies to Freedom of Information requests. Any training provided by or on behalf of the British Government complies with our domestic and international human rights obligations.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2018-10-15T15:07:07.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980162/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980162/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-10-01","Bahrain: Technical Assistance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether human rights risk assessments are required to be made before funds are provided under the Integrated Activity Fund (IAF); whether any such assessments were made before funding was provided to Bahrain under the IAF; if so, whether any such assessment will be made public; and if not, why not.","false","Biography information for Lord Scriven",,"Lord Scriven","HL10431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980163","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-10-15","<p>The UK and the Republic of Cyprus are engaged in ongoing constructive discussions on the future of the SBAs. We aim to ensure that those living and working in the SBAs, in particular the 11,000 Cypriot residents, are not adversely impacted by the UK’s withdrawal from the EU. We are confident that an agreement can be reached which respects the Treaty of Establishment, and safeguards both the lives of citizens, and the effective military functioning of the bases.</p>",,"Lord Callanan",,"2018-10-15T12:58:30.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980163/answer","Biography information for Lord Callanan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980163/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-10-01","Cyprus: Military Bases","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what changes they anticipate will be needed to the arrangements for crossing the border between the Cypriot UK Sovereign Bases and the Republic of Cyprus after the UK leaves the EU; what preparations are being made to make any such changes; and what discussions they have had with the EU and the Republic of Cyprus on the issue.","false","Biography information for Lord Sharkey",,"Lord Sharkey","HL10432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980164","Department for Education","false","2018-10-12","<p>We estimate that there were 13,000 funded learners aged 19-24 who participated in Access to higher education (HE) courses in the 2015-2016 academic year in England through the adult skills budget. £37 million of the adult skills budget has been spent on delivering Access to HE courses.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton","HL10434","2018-10-12T11:18:36.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980164/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980164/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-01","Adult Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how much of the adult education budget in England was spent on access to higher education courses for 19–24 year olds in 2015–16.","false","Biography information for Lord Smith of Clifton",,"Lord Smith of Clifton","HL10433"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980165","Department for Education","false","2018-10-12","<p>We estimate that there were 13,000 funded learners aged 19-24 who participated in Access to higher education (HE) courses in the 2015-2016 academic year in England through the adult skills budget. £37 million of the adult skills budget has been spent on delivering Access to HE courses.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Agnew of Oulton","HL10433","2018-10-12T11:18:36.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980165/answer","Biography information for Lord Agnew of Oulton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/980165/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-01","Adult Education","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how many students aged 19–24 were on access to higher education courses funded via the adult education budget in England in 2015–16.","false","Biography information for Lord Smith of Clifton",,"Lord Smith of Clifton","HL10434"
